    				Past Companies    			





Company
About
Position



Praja
PRAJA was conceived and cofounded, with C.K. Prahalad, based on research at UCSD. PRAJA was the leading provider of infrastructure software technology for development of event-based information management. PRAJA worked with several companies, including Yahoo and GM. PRAJA was acquired by Tibco in September 2002.
CTO, President, CEO, Co-Founder



Virage
The Virage platform enables the integration of streaming video with value-added applications such as advertising, pay-per-view, subscription and syndication. Virage became a public company (NASDAQ: VRGE) in June 2000.
CEO, Chairman, Director



NX Imageware
This company was dedicated to linking virtual and physical worlds by providing solutions for surface modeling, reverse engineering, rapid prototyping and inspection. The company was the leader in its domain and automobile and aerospace industries. The company was acquired by SDRC in 1998. Now the leading surfacing products from SDRC are based on ImageWare products.
Chairman, Director
















